{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":984,"text":"Shall I ask for a show\nof hands or a clapping"},{"time":6144,"text":"of people in different generations?"},{"time":8268,"text":"I'm interested in how many\nare three to 12 years old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":17274,"text":"None, huh?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18584,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":19983,"text":"All right."},{"time":21809,"text":"I'm going to talk about dinosaurs."},{"time":23591,"text":"Do you remember dinosaurs\nwhen you were that age?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33595,"text":"Dinosaurs are kind of funny, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38521,"text":"We're going to kind of go\nin a different direction right now."},{"time":41454,"text":"I hope you all realize that."},{"time":43554,"text":"So I'll just give you my message up front:"},{"time":46355,"text":"Try not to go extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47994,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49356,"text":"That's it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50566,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55919,"text":"People ask me a lot --"},{"time":58014,"text":"in fact, one of the most asked\nquestions I get"},{"time":60690,"text":"is, why do children\nlike dinosaurs so much?"},{"time":64000,"text":"What's the fascination?"},{"time":66481,"text":"And I usually just say,"},{"time":69000,"text":"\"Well, dinosaurs were big,"},{"time":71831,"text":"different and gone.\""},{"time":75196,"text":"They're all gone."},{"time":76518,"text":"Well that's not true,"},{"time":78588,"text":"but we'll get to the goose in a minute."},{"time":80747,"text":"So that's sort of the theme:"},{"time":83268,"text":"big, different and gone."},{"time":87144,"text":"The title of my talk:"},{"time":88833,"text":"Shape-shifting Dinosaurs:"},{"time":90899,"text":"The cause of a premature extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94005,"text":"Now I assume that we remember dinosaurs."},{"time":96818,"text":"And there's lots of different shapes."},{"time":99745,"text":"Lots of different kinds."},{"time":102222,"text":"A long time ago,"},{"time":104690,"text":"back in the early 1900s,\nmuseums were out looking for dinosaurs."},{"time":109862,"text":"They went out and gathered them up."},{"time":112601,"text":"And this is an interesting story."},{"time":115203,"text":"Every museum wanted a little bigger\nor better one than anybody else had."},{"time":119258,"text":"So if the museum in Toronto went out\nand collected a Tyrannosaur, a big one,"},{"time":126070,"text":"then the museum in Ottawa\nwanted a bigger one, and a better one."},{"time":130792,"text":"And that happened for all museums."},{"time":132644,"text":"So everyone was out looking\nfor all these bigger and better dinosaurs."},{"time":137901,"text":"And this was in the early 1900s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141146,"text":"By about 1970,"},{"time":144861,"text":"some scientists were sitting around\nand they thought, \"What in the world --"},{"time":149715,"text":"Look at these dinosaurs, they're all big."},{"time":153752,"text":"Where are all the little ones?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":155746,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158574,"text":"And they thought about it\nand they even wrote papers about it:"},{"time":162114,"text":"\"Where are the little dinosaurs?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172899,"text":"Well, go to a museum, you'll see,"},{"time":176540,"text":"see how many baby dinosaurs there are."},{"time":179662,"text":"People assumed --\nand this was actually a problem --"},{"time":182473,"text":"people assumed\nthat if they had little dinosaurs,"},{"time":186801,"text":"if they had juvenile dinosaurs,\nthey'd be easy to identify."},{"time":190527,"text":"You'd have a big dinosaur\nand a littler dinosaur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194424,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":195866,"text":"But all they had were big dinosaurs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198983,"text":"And it comes down to a couple of things."},{"time":201000,"text":"First off, scientists have egos,"},{"time":205778,"text":"and scientists like to name dinosaurs."},{"time":209655,"text":"They like to name anything."},{"time":211000,"text":"Everybody likes to have\ntheir own animal that they named."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214981,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217982,"text":"And so every time they found something\nthat looked a little different,"},{"time":221313,"text":"they named it something different."},{"time":223668,"text":"And what happened, of course,"},{"time":225094,"text":"is we ended up with a whole\nbunch of different dinosaurs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230642,"text":"In 1975,"},{"time":234296,"text":"a light went on in somebody's head."},{"time":236829,"text":"Dr. Peter Dodson\nat the University of Pennsylvania"},{"time":241078,"text":"actually realized that dinosaurs\ngrew kind of like birds do,"},{"time":248668,"text":"which is different\nthan the way reptiles grow."},{"time":252246,"text":"And in fact,"},{"time":253850,"text":"he used the cassowary as an example."},{"time":257390,"text":"And it's kind of cool --\nif you look at the cassowary,"},{"time":260465,"text":"or any of the birds\nthat have crests on their heads,"},{"time":263716,"text":"they grow to about 80 percent adult size\nbefore the crest starts to grow."},{"time":271434,"text":"Now think about that."},{"time":273000,"text":"They're basically retaining\ntheir juvenile characteristics"},{"time":276000,"text":"very late in what we call ontogeny."},{"time":279544,"text":"So allometric cranial ontogeny\nis relative skull growth."},{"time":286000,"text":"So you can see that if you actually found\none that was 80 percent grown"},{"time":293461,"text":"and you didn't know that it was going\nto grow up to a cassowary,"},{"time":296910,"text":"you would think\nthey were two different animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300170,"text":"So this was a problem,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and Peter Dodson pointed this out\nusing some duck-billed dinosaurs"},{"time":309062,"text":"then called Hypacrosaurus."},{"time":310587,"text":"And he showed that if you were to take\na baby and an adult"},{"time":315477,"text":"and make an average\nof what it should look like,"},{"time":318802,"text":"if it grew in sort of a linear fashion,"},{"time":322053,"text":"it would have a crest\nabout half the size of the adult."},{"time":326236,"text":"But the actual subadult at 65 percent\nhad no crest at all."},{"time":332321,"text":"So this was interesting."},{"time":334000,"text":"So this is where people went astray again."},{"time":340111,"text":"I mean, if they'd have just taken that,"},{"time":342742,"text":"taken Peter Dodson's work,\nand gone on with that,"},{"time":345784,"text":"then we would have a lot less\ndinosaurs than we have."},{"time":349658,"text":"But scientists have egos;\nthey like to name things."},{"time":354120,"text":"And so they went on naming dinosaurs\nbecause they were different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360145,"text":"Now we have a way of actually testing"},{"time":362822,"text":"to see whether a dinosaur, or any animal,\nis a young one or an older one."},{"time":368141,"text":"And that's by actually\ncutting into their bones."},{"time":371889,"text":"But cutting into the bones of a dinosaur\nis hard to do, as you can imagine,"},{"time":378687,"text":"because in museums, bones are precious."},{"time":385842,"text":"You go into a museum,\nand they take really good care of them."},{"time":388724,"text":"They put them in foam, little containers."},{"time":392340,"text":"They're very well taken care of."},{"time":396172,"text":"They don't like it if you come in\nand want to saw them open and look inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400110,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":401135,"text":"So they don't normally let you do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404568,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":405593,"text":"But I have a museum\nand I collect dinosaurs"},{"time":410127,"text":"and I can saw mine open."},{"time":412015,"text":"So that's what I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414016,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420705,"text":"So if you cut open a little dinosaur,"},{"time":423386,"text":"it's very spongy inside, like A."},{"time":426100,"text":"And if you cut into an older dinosaur,\nit's very massive."},{"time":429000,"text":"You can tell it's mature bone."},{"time":432101,"text":"So it's real easy to tell them apart."},{"time":434604,"text":"So what I want to do is show you these."},{"time":438333,"text":"In North America in the northern plains\nof the United States"},{"time":442258,"text":"and the southern plains\nof Alberta and Saskatchewan,"},{"time":446000,"text":"there's this unit of rock\ncalled the Hell Creek Formation"},{"time":449750,"text":"that produces the last\ndinosaurs that lived on Earth."},{"time":453225,"text":"And there are 12 of them\nthat everyone recognizes --"},{"time":456173,"text":"I mean the 12 primary dinosaurs\nthat went extinct."},{"time":460613,"text":"And so we will evaluate them."},{"time":464139,"text":"And that's sort of what I've been doing."},{"time":466119,"text":"So my students, my staff,\nwe've been cutting them open."},{"time":471814,"text":"Now as you can imagine,\ncutting open a leg bone is one thing,"},{"time":475681,"text":"but when you go to a museum"},{"time":478764,"text":"and say, \"You don't mind if I cut open\nyour dinosaur's skull, do you?\""},{"time":483454,"text":"they say, \"Go away.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493548,"text":"So here are 12 dinosaurs."},{"time":495000,"text":"And we want to look at these three first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498745,"text":"So these are dinosaurs\nthat are called Pachycephalosaurus."},{"time":502143,"text":"And everybody knows\nthat these three animals are related."},{"time":505797,"text":"And the assumption is that they're related\nlike cousins or whatever."},{"time":512122,"text":"But no one ever considered\nthat they might be more closely related."},{"time":517982,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":519230,"text":"people looked at them\nand they saw the differences."},{"time":522585,"text":"And you all know\nthat if you are going to determine"},{"time":526000,"text":"whether you're related\nto your brother or your sister,"},{"time":528930,"text":"you can't do it by looking at differences."},{"time":532690,"text":"You can only determine relatedness\nby looking for similarities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536215,"text":"So people were looking at these"},{"time":538238,"text":"and they were talking\nabout how different they are."},{"time":540695,"text":"Pachycephalosaurus has a big,\nthick dome on its head,"},{"time":544143,"text":"and it's got some little bumps\non the back of its head,"},{"time":546864,"text":"and it's got a bunch of gnarly things\non the end of its nose."},{"time":550790,"text":"And then Stygimoloch, another dinosaur\nfrom the same age, lived at the same time,"},{"time":556570,"text":"has spikes sticking out\nthe back of its head."},{"time":558760,"text":"It's got a little, tiny dome,"},{"time":560756,"text":"and it's got a bunch\nof gnarly stuff on its nose."},{"time":564289,"text":"And then there's this thing\ncalled Dracorex hogwartsia."},{"time":569227,"text":"Guess where that came from?"},{"time":570681,"text":"Dragon."},{"time":571869,"text":"So here's a dinosaur that has spikes\nsticking out of its head,"},{"time":575645,"text":"no dome and gnarly stuff on its nose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579484,"text":"Nobody noticed the gnarly stuff\nsort of looked alike."},{"time":583102,"text":"But they did look at these three"},{"time":584725,"text":"and they said, \"These\nare three different dinosaurs,"},{"time":587204,"text":"and Dracorex is probably\nthe most primitive of them."},{"time":590142,"text":"And the other one\nis more primitive than the other.\""},{"time":594156,"text":"It's unclear to me how they actually\nsorted these three of them out."},{"time":598281,"text":"But if you line them up,"},{"time":600198,"text":"if you just take those three skulls\nand just line them up,"},{"time":603277,"text":"they line up like this."},{"time":605288,"text":"Dracorex is the littlest one,"},{"time":607368,"text":"Stygimoloch is the middle-size one,"},{"time":610001,"text":"Pachycephalosaurus is the largest one."},{"time":612000,"text":"And one would think,\nthat should give me a clue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618353,"text":"But it didn't give them a clue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619907,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621105,"text":"Because, well we know why."},{"time":624204,"text":"Scientists like to name things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628668,"text":"So if we cut open Dracorex --"},{"time":631428,"text":"I cut open our Dracorex --"},{"time":633377,"text":"and look, it was spongy inside,\nreally spongy inside."},{"time":637625,"text":"I mean, it is a juvenile\nand it's growing really fast."},{"time":641904,"text":"So it is going to get bigger."},{"time":643915,"text":"If you cut open Stygimoloch,\nit is doing the same thing."},{"time":647577,"text":"The dome, that little dome,\nis growing really fast."},{"time":651231,"text":"It's inflating very fast."},{"time":653564,"text":"What's interesting is the spike\non the back of the Dracorex"},{"time":656964,"text":"was growing very fast as well."},{"time":659067,"text":"The spikes on the back of the Stygimoloch\nare actually resorbing,"},{"time":662340,"text":"which means they're getting smaller\nas that dome is getting bigger."},{"time":666498,"text":"And if we look at Pachycephalosaurus,"},{"time":669000,"text":"Pachycephalosaurus has a solid dome"},{"time":672275,"text":"and its little bumps on the back\nof its head were also resorbing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677267,"text":"So just with these three dinosaurs,"},{"time":681000,"text":"as a scientist, we can easily hypothesize"},{"time":683720,"text":"that it is just a growth series\nof the same animal."},{"time":689199,"text":"Which of course means"},{"time":692962,"text":"that Stygimoloch and Dracorex are extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697705,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702693,"text":"OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704054,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":706947,"text":"Which of course means\nwe have 10 primary dinosaurs to deal with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713234,"text":"So a colleague of mine at Berkeley --\nhe and I were looking at Triceratops."},{"time":718195,"text":"And before the year 2000 --"},{"time":720534,"text":"now remember, Triceratops was first\nfound in the 1800s --"},{"time":724230,"text":"before 2000, no one had ever seen\na juvenile Triceratops."},{"time":730362,"text":"There's a Triceratops\nin every museum in the world,"},{"time":733930,"text":"but no one had ever collected a juvenile."},{"time":738418,"text":"And we know why, right?"},{"time":739844,"text":"Because everybody wants to have a big one."},{"time":742844,"text":"So everyone had a big one."},{"time":744902,"text":"So we went out and collected\na whole bunch of stuff"},{"time":747334,"text":"and we found a whole bunch of little ones."},{"time":749365,"text":"They're everywhere,\nthey're all over the place."},{"time":752584,"text":"So we have a whole bunch\nof them at our museum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754873,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759347,"text":"And everybody says\nit's because I have a little museum."},{"time":762035,"text":"When you have a little museum,\nyou have little dinosaurs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764779,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":767889,"text":"If you look at the Triceratops,"},{"time":769655,"text":"you can see it's changing,\nit's shape-shifting."},{"time":772324,"text":"As the juveniles are growing up,\ntheir horns actually curve backwards."},{"time":776236,"text":"And then as they get older,\nthe horns grow forward."},{"time":779925,"text":"And that's pretty cool."},{"time":781328,"text":"If you look along the edge of the frill,"},{"time":783667,"text":"they have these little triangular bones\nthat actually grow big as triangles"},{"time":788857,"text":"and then they flatten against the frill"},{"time":791585,"text":"pretty much like the spikes do\non the Pachycephalosaurs."},{"time":795818,"text":"And then, because the juveniles\nare in my collection,"},{"time":800323,"text":"I cut them open ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801827,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":803002,"text":"and look inside."},{"time":804200,"text":"And the little one is really spongy."},{"time":807369,"text":"And the middle-size one is really spongy."},{"time":809767,"text":"But what was interesting\nwas the adult Triceratops was also spongy."},{"time":814666,"text":"And this is a skull\nthat is two meters long."},{"time":818113,"text":"It's a big skull."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820828,"text":"But there's another dinosaur\nthat is found in this formation"},{"time":825619,"text":"that looks like a Triceratops,\nexcept it's bigger,"},{"time":829126,"text":"and it's called Torosaurus."},{"time":831955,"text":"And Torosaurus, when we cut\ninto it, has mature bone."},{"time":836437,"text":"But it's got these big\nholes in its shield."},{"time":838503,"text":"And everybody says,"},{"time":839680,"text":"\"A Triceratops and a Torosaurus\ncan't possibly be the same animal"},{"time":843364,"text":"because one of them's bigger\nthan the other one.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":845880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":850539,"text":"\"And it has holes in its frill.\""},{"time":853036,"text":"And I said, \"Well do we have\nany juvenile Torosauruses?\""},{"time":856019,"text":"And they said, \"Well, no,\nbut it has holes in its frill.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":861463,"text":"So one of my graduate\nstudents, John Scannella,"},{"time":864939,"text":"looked through our whole collection"},{"time":866682,"text":"and he actually discovered that the hole\nstarting to form in Triceratops"},{"time":872822,"text":"and, of course it's open, in Torosaurus --"},{"time":875981,"text":"so he found the transitional ones\nbetween Triceratops and Torosaurus,"},{"time":881143,"text":"which was pretty cool."},{"time":882399,"text":"So now we know that Torosaurus\nis actually a grown-up Triceratops."},{"time":889964,"text":"Now when we name dinosaurs,"},{"time":891768,"text":"when we name anything,\nthe original name gets to stick"},{"time":895328,"text":"and the second name is thrown out."},{"time":899936,"text":"So Torosaurus is extinct."},{"time":903441,"text":"Triceratops, if you've heard the news,\na lot of the newscasters got it all wrong."},{"time":907283,"text":"They thought Torosaurus should be kept\nand Triceratops thrown out,"},{"time":910857,"text":"but that's not going to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912665,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918179,"text":"All right, so we can do this\nwith a bunch of dinosaurs."},{"time":921486,"text":"I mean, here's Edmontosaurus"},{"time":923556,"text":"and Anatotitan."},{"time":925423,"text":"Anatotitan: giant duck."},{"time":928632,"text":"It's a giant duck-bill dinosaur."},{"time":930807,"text":"Here's another one."},{"time":932559,"text":"So we look at the bone histology."},{"time":935056,"text":"The bone histology tells us\nthat Edmontosaurus is a juvenile,"},{"time":939963,"text":"or at least a subadult,"},{"time":941615,"text":"and the other one is an adult,\nand we have an ontogeny."},{"time":948273,"text":"And we get rid of Anatotitan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951400,"text":"So we can just keep doing this."},{"time":953245,"text":"And the last one is T. Rex."},{"time":957332,"text":"So there's these two dinosaurs,\nT. Rex and Nanotyrannus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":964914,"text":"Again, it makes you wonder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967654,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":970888,"text":"But they had a good question."},{"time":973247,"text":"They were looking at them and they said,\n\"One's got 17 teeth,"},{"time":976156,"text":"and the biggest one's got 12 teeth."},{"time":978044,"text":"And that doesn't make any sense at all,"},{"time":979938,"text":"because we don't know of any dinosaurs\nthat gain teeth as they get older."},{"time":983630,"text":"So it must be true --"},{"time":985902,"text":"they must be different.\""},{"time":988643,"text":"So we cut into them."},{"time":991373,"text":"And sure enough,\nNanotyrannus has juvenile bone"},{"time":995274,"text":"and the bigger one has more mature bone."},{"time":999439,"text":"It looks like it could still get bigger."},{"time":1001866,"text":"And at the Museum\nof the Rockies where we work,"},{"time":1004111,"text":"I have four T. rexes,\nso I can cut a whole bunch of them."},{"time":1007774,"text":"But I didn't have to cut\nany of them really,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"because I just lined up their jaws"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and it turned out\nthe biggest one had 12 teeth"},{"time":1016334,"text":"and the next smallest one had 13"},{"time":1018533,"text":"and the next smallest had 14."},{"time":1020787,"text":"And of course, Nano has 17."},{"time":1022834,"text":"And we just went out and looked\nat other people's collections"},{"time":1025745,"text":"and we found one that has\nsort of 15 teeth."},{"time":1029504,"text":"So again, real easy to say"},{"time":1032306,"text":"that Tyrannosaurus ontogeny\nincluded Nanotyrannus,"},{"time":1037686,"text":"and therefore we can take out\nanother dinosaur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042349,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047377,"text":"So when it comes down\nto our end Cretaceous,"},{"time":1050694,"text":"we have seven left."},{"time":1054099,"text":"And that's a good number."},{"time":1055756,"text":"That's a good number\nto go extinct, I think."},{"time":1059604,"text":"Now as you can imagine,"},{"time":1060862,"text":"this is not very popular\nwith fourth-graders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063743,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064768,"text":"Fourth-graders love their dinosaurs,\nthey memorize them."},{"time":1073113,"text":"And they're not happy with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074867,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077507,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078722,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}